OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F333A1781887672
OL,3,CThree inmates found guilty of
OL,4,Cmurdering child killer
OL,6,FThree prisoners have been found guilty
OL,7,Fof murdering a child killer who was
OL,8,Fstabbed to death in his prison cell.
OL,10,FThirty-three-year-old Kyle Bevan was
OL,11,Fstabbed 25 times during the attack in
OL,12,FNovember last year at HMP Wakefield by
OL,13,Fconvicted killers 45-year-old Mark
OL,14,FFellows, 57-year-old Lee Newell and 64-
OL,15,Fyear-old David Taylor.
OL,17,FBevan was serving a life sentence with
OL,18,Fa minimum tariff of 28 years for
OL,19,Fmurdering his partner's two-year-old
OL,20,Fdaughter, Lola James, in
OL,21,FHaverfordwest, Pembrokeshire, in 2020.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G1/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,334,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33302
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F333A1781887672
OL,3,CThree inmates found guilty of
OL,4,Cmurdering child killer
OL,6,FFellows, Newell and Taylor were seen
OL,7,Fon CCTV following Bevan into his cell
OL,8,Fafter 5.30pm on 4 November.
OL,9,FProsecutors say they emerged less than
OL,10,Ffive minutes later in "a satisfied,
OL,11,Fjob-done mood" and left Bevan "tidily
OL,12,Ftucked up in bed".
OL,14,FHe was not discovered until the
OL,15,Ffollowing morning when prison staff
OL,16,Fwere told by an inmate that "something
OL,17,Fwas wrong with Bevan".
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G2/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,334,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33303
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F333A1781887672
OL,3,CThree inmates found guilty of
OL,4,Cmurdering child killer
OL,6,FLeeds Crown Court heard that Bevan
OL,7,Fbled to death after injuries caused by
OL,8,Fat least two different weapons and
OL,9,Fthat there was "a lot of tension in
OL,10,Fthe prison at the time".
OL,12,FIn the weeks leading up to Bevan's
OL,13,Fdeath at HMP Wakefield, paedophile
OL,14,FLostprophets singer Ian Watkins was
OL,15,Falso stabbed to death.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G3/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,334,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33304
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F333A1781887672
OL,3,CThree inmates found guilty of
OL,4,Cmurdering child killer
OL,6,FThe court heard the three defendants
OL,7,Fhad a hostility to people who had
OL,8,Fcommitted offences against children
OL,9,Fand Fellows and Newell had expressed a
OL,10,Fdesire to be transferred away from
OL,11,FWakefield.
OL,13,FIn his closing speech during the
OL,14,Ftrial, prosecutor Jason Pitter KC said
OL,15,FNewell had previously strangled a
OL,16,Fprisoner who murdered a child and left
OL,17,Fhim in his bed, telling jurors there
OL,18,Fwas "a chilling similarity to that and
OL,19,Fthe circumstances of Kyle Bevan's
OL,20,Fdeath".
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G4/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,334,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33305
SC,0005
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F333A1781887672
OL,3,CThree inmates found guilty of
OL,4,Cmurdering child killer
OL,6,FFellows, known as "the Wakefield
OL,7,FDexter" and "the Iceman", had
OL,8,Fpreviously committed two murders "to
OL,9,Ftake out people he was opposed to or
OL,10,Fdid not like"..
OL,12,FWhile Taylor had recently been
OL,13,Ftransferred to Wakefield in relation
OL,14,Fto the murder of an associate, to
OL,15,Fwhich he pleaded guilty, and the
OL,16,Fattempted murder of a police officer
OL,17,Fwhile he was in custody.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G5/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,334,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33306
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F333A1781887672
OL,3,CThree inmates found guilty of
OL,4,Cmurdering child killer
OL,6,FThe court heard Taylor boasted about
OL,7,Fhis ability to make makeshift weapons
OL,8,Fand after Bevan's death some were
OL,9,Ffound in a bottle of chilli sauce in
OL,10,Fhis cell, although they could not be
OL,11,Fmatched to the fatal attack.
OL,13,FJurors heard that unlike other jails,
OL,14,Fvulnerable prisoners were not
OL,15,Fseparated from other inmates at
OL,16,FWakefield.
OL,18,FLeeds Crown Court heard that Bevan
OL,19,F"kept himself to himself" and would
OL,20,Fmainly stay in his cell, often asking
OL,21,Fto be locked inside, jurors were told.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G6/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,334,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33307
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F333A1781887672
OL,3,CThree inmates found guilty of
OL,4,Cmurdering child killer
OL,6,FOn the day of his death, he was seen
OL,7,Fon CCTV walking to his cell, followed
OL,8,Fby the three defendants and Taylor who
OL,9,Fcould be seen taking something from
OL,10,Fhis waistband as he went in.
OL,12,FSumming up the case to jurors, the
OL,13,Fjudge, Mrs Justice McGowan, said: "We
OL,14,Fdo not know who did what in the cell.
OL,15,FAt least one person must have
OL,16,Finflicted the fatal injuries."
OL,18,F"He was stabbed to either side of his
OL,19,Fneck and repeatedly to the front of
OL,20,Fhis body."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G7/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,334,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33308
SC,0008
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F333A1781887672
OL,3,CThree inmates found guilty of
OL,4,Cmurdering child killer
OL,6,FThe court heard the three defendants
OL,7,Fleft the cell less than five minutes
OL,8,Flater "as if nothing had happened",
OL,9,Fshaking hands and apparently
OL,10,Fcongratulating each other.
OL,12,FNewell had an injury to his hand while
OL,13,FFellows could be seen rolling up his
OL,14,Ftracksuit bottoms after realising they
OL,15,Fhad blood on them, and later disposing
OL,16,Fof them.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G8/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,334,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33309
SC,0009
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F333A1781887672
OL,3,CThree inmates found guilty of
OL,4,Cmurdering child killer
OL,6,FJurors heard one weapon, made from a
OL,7,Ffolded piece of metal from the back of
OL,8,Fa television, was thrown from Bevan's
OL,9,Fcell and found on the ground outside.
OL,10,FIt had Bevan's blood on it.
OL,12,FThe weapon which caused the fatal
OL,13,Finjuries has never been found.
OL,15,FBefore sending the jurors out to
OL,16,Fconsider the verdicts, Mrs Justice
OL,17,FMcGowan said: "This case is about the
OL,18,Fdeath of Kyle Bevan.
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1         G9/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,334,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33310
SC,0010
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F333A1781887672
OL,3,CThree inmates found guilty of
OL,4,Cmurdering child killer
OL,6,F"It is not about whether mixing
OL,7,Fvulnerable prisoners and main
OL,8,Fprisoners is a good way to run a
OL,9,Fprison.
OL,11,F"It is not about whether these
OL,12,Fdefendants or anyone else has a view
OL,13,Fabout how people who commit offences
OL,14,Fagainst children should be punished.
OL,16,F"Nobody has a right to kill anyone
OL,17,Felse because they disapprove of what
OL,18,Fthey have done, or because they hate
OL,19,Fthem. It's a fairly basic premise in a
OL,20,Fcivilised society."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1        G10/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BYorks News CReg TV FThis Day
FL,334,330,260,120,000,100
PN,33311
SC,0011
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F333A1781887672
OL,3,CThree inmates found guilty of
OL,4,Cmurdering child killer
OL,6,FSenior investigating officer, Chief
OL,7,FInspector James Entwistle said: "This
OL,8,Fwas a premeditated brutal attack
OL,9,Fcarried out inside a prison by three
OL,10,Flong-term inmates.
OL,12,F"Fellows, Taylor and Newell's actions
OL,13,Fshowed a complete disregard for life
OL,14,Fand for the rules designed to keep
OL,15,Fpeople safe in custody.
OL,17,F"Today's verdicts ensure the continued
OL,18,Fsafety of others by holding these
OL,19,Fdangerous individuals to account and
OL,20,Fensuring they face the full weight of
OL,21,Fthe law."
OL,1,Woz5~k4{$z%~s1z5jw=hw1        G11/12
OL,2,W,.!+.!/*%/*%,.!/*%/*%/"-$T,,,,,,,,,,,,,
